This paper deals with reinforcement learning algorithms and their application to robotics tasks. Specifically, it focuses on the use of trajectory optimization methods for exploration in Deep Deterministic Policy Gradient (DDPG) when trained on a latent image embedding. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the following sub-categories:

- cs.LG (Machine Learning): This sub-category covers papers that deal with the development of machine learning algorithms and their applications. The use of DDPG and trajectory optimization methods for exploration falls under this category.
- cs.RO (Robotics): This sub-category covers papers that deal with the development of robotic systems and their applications. The paper focuses on training a Baxter robot to perform an insertion task, which suggests that it belongs to this category.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): This sub-category covers papers that deal with the development of artificial intelligence algorithms and their applications. The use of reinforcement learning algorithms and trajectory optimization methods falls under this category.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): This sub-category covers papers that deal with computer vision and image processing. The paper makes use of a latent image embedding, which suggests that it belongs to this category.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): This sub-category covers papers that deal with the development of control systems and their applications. The paper deals with the use of reinforcement learning algorithms for control, which suggests that it belongs to this category
